\textit{Clinical entity analysis}: We use gpt-4o-mini to extract five entity categories; Symptoms, Diagnoses, Substances and Habits, Procedures and Tests, Treatments from both generated summary and doctor-patient conversation. We also normalize morphological variants to canonical forms. An entity generated from the summary is a true positive (TP) if it is semantically equivalent to an entity generated from the dialogue; a false positive (FP, or \textit{hallucination}) if it appears in the generated summary but not the dialogue; a false negative (FN, or \textit{omission}) if an entity present in dialogue is absent in the generated summary. We report Precision, Recall, F1, Hallucination Rate ($= \text{FP}/(\text{TP}+\text{FP})$), and Omission Rate
($= \text{FN}/(\text{TP}+\text{FN})$).





