The performance gap that was real and sizable under prompting is essentially eliminated by fine-tuning. This is an important result for equity: the gap is not inherent to the languages, it is an artifact of insufficient task-specific training.

The hallucination reductions are equally striking. Macro-average hallucination drops from 42.4\% to 10.5\% for Qwen and from 50.9\% to 9.8\% for Mistral. Mistral-Telugu, which had a hallucination rate of 71.8\% at zero-shot, meaning nearly three-quarters of generated clinical entities were ungrounded falls to 7.0\% post fine-tuning,
